ual%20reality%20services%20to%20Arizona%20and%20parts%20of%20Michigan%2C%20The%20New%20Yorker%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20field%20trip%20to%20Everest%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20school%20instructs%20students%20through%20a%20combination%20of%20virtual%20reality%20sessions%20and%20online%20classes.%20Those%20from%20third%20to%20eighth%20grade%20are%20given%20Meta%20Quest%202%20headsets%20that%20they%20wear%20for%2030%20to%2040-minute%20sessions%20up%20to%20five%20times%20a%20day%2C%20the%20publication%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20these%20sessions%2C%20students%20spend%20their%20days%20completing%20coursework%20independently%20and%20correspond%20with%20teachers%20online.%20Instruction%20for%20kindergarten%20through%20second%20grade%20is%20more%20similar%20to%20virtual%20school%20where%20classes%20are%20both%20live%20and%20pre-recorded%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.optimaacademy.online%2Fonline-elementary-school%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Optima's%20website.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOptima%20Academy%20offers%20about%20250%20custom%20virtual%20environments%2C%20and%20also%20sells%20access%20to%20these%20environments%20to%20other%20independent%20schools%2C%20The%20New%20Yorker%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20episode%20recounted%20in%20the%20report%2C%20students%20in%20a%20sixth%20grade%20science%20class%20were%20taken%20on%20a%20virtual%20field%20trip%20to%20a%20Everest%20base%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20virtual%20environment%20was%20%26quot%3Belaborately%20staged%26quot%3B%20with%20gray%20tents%2C%20sleeping%20bags%2C%20and%20sounds%20of%20wind%20in%20the%20background%2C%20the%20trip%20didn't%20go%20as%20planned%2C%20the%20New%20Yorker%20reported.%20The%20students%20struggled%20with%20the%20lesson%2C%20and%20had%20difficulties%20coordinating%20with%20each%20other%20through%20various%20activities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20also%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirtual-reality-vr-side-effects-2018-3%5C%22%3EVR%20headsets%20can%20cause%20%26quot%3Bsimulator%20sickness%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bcybersickness%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20similar%20to%20motion%20sickness.%20Studies%20have%20also%20shown%20that%20prolonged%20periods%20of%20VR%20use%20could%20even%20result%20in%20%26quot%3Breality%20blurring%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20users%20have%20trouble%20distinguishing%20between%20virtual%20reality%20and%20real%20life%2C%20Jeremy%20Bailenson%2C%20the%20director%20of%20Stanford's%20Virtual%20Human%20Interaction%20Lab%2C%20told%20The%20New%20Yorker.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20founders%20suggest%20that%20school%20shouldn't%20be%20a%20student's%20whole%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20drawbacks%20of%20virtual%20learning%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fschools-choose-between-bad-online-learning-and-unsafe-classrooms-2020-7%5C%22%3Eonline%2C%20remote%20learning%20on%20the%20whole%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20the%20absence%20of%20human%20interaction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20attending%20Optima%2C%20though%2C%20told%20The%20New%20Yorker%20that%20it%20can%20be%20a%20reprieve%20for%20students%20with%20social%20anxiety%20or%20have%20been%20bullied.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOptima's%20co-founder%20Adam%20Mangana%20told%20The%20New%20Yorker%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20schoolhouse%20is%20expected%20to%20provide%20so%20much.%20A%20good%20life%20for%20a%20student%20is%20more%20decentralized.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-company-offers-virtual-reality-alternative-to-public-schools-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693685797000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f3856f7819260019109007%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22origi