ible%20border%20that%20divides%20the%20two%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20Frelick%20wrote%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2F01%2Fsaudis-newest-horror-involves-shooting-shelling-migrants-border%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20piece%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20Friday%20by%20The%20Hill.%20%26quot%3BThese%20migrants%20include%20large%20numbers%20of%20women%20and%20children.%20They%20are%20unarmed.%20Hundreds%2C%20perhaps%20thousands%2C%20have%20been%20killed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20report%2C%20HRW%20cited%20eyewitnesses%20who%20reported%20migrants%20being%20struck%20by%20mortar%20fire%20as%20they%20approached%20the%20Saudi%20border.%20One%20person%20said%20that%20an%20attack%20on%20a%20group%20of%20170%20migrants%20left%20more%20than%20half%20of%20them%20dead%2C%20according%20to%20HRW%2C%20appearing%20to%20reflect%20a%20conscious%20decision%20to%20discourage%20migration%20through%20targeted%20killings%20%E2%80%94%20and%20raising%20the%20prospect%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bstate%20policy%20of%20deliberate%20murder%20of%20a%20civilian%20population.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaudi%20Arabia%20has%20denied%20the%20allegation.%20But%20according%20to%20The%20Washington%20Post%2C%20rumors%20of%20the%20killings%20had%20been%20circulating%20among%20diplomats%20%26quot%3Bfor%20more%20than%20a%20year%26quot%3B%20prior%20to%20the%20HRW%20report.%20Michal%20Ratney%2C%20US%20ambassador%20to%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20discussed%20the%20allegations%20last%20month%20%E2%80%94%20ahead%20of%20the%20report's%20release%20%E2%80%94%20and%20US%20officials%20are%20now%20trying%20to%20determine%20whether%20the%20units%20accused%20received%20training%20or%20weapons%20from%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEthiopia%20has%20also%20said%20it%20is%20investigating%20the%20allegations%2C%20%26quot%3Bin%20tandem%20with%20the%20Saudi%20authorities%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F08%2F23%2F1195377365%2Fethiopia-to-investigate-report-of-killings-of-its-nationals-at-the-saudi-yemen-b%5C%22%3Eper%20the%20Associated%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20news%20tip%3F%20Email%20this%20reporter%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acdavis%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecdavis%40insider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-investigation-us-military-aid-saudi-arabia-massacre-migrants-yemen-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693671526000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f358f91b7ced0019c76591%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-investigation-us-military-aid-saudi-arabia-massacre-migrants-yemen-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Human%20Rights%20Watch%20has%20accused%20Saudi%20Arabia%20of%20killing%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%26quot%3B%20of%20migrants%20and%20asylum%20seekers%20near%20the%20Yemen%20border.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Charles%20R.%20Davis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A123%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-investigation-us-military-aid-saudi-arabia-massacre-migrants-yemen-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Panel%20on%20'One%20Election'%20to%20Examine%20if%20%E2%80%98Ratification%20by%20States%E2%80%99%20Is%20Needed%2C%20Adhir%20Declines%20to%20Be%20on%20it%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F25204736%2FScreen-Shot-2020-01-25-at-8.47.13-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20has%20notified%20an%20eight-member%20high-level%20committee%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fone-nation-one-election-fourth-committee%5C%22%3Eexamine%20the%C2%A0%20proposition%20of%20one%20election%20simultaneously%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20the%20union%20and%20all%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20most%20crucial%20point%20among%20the%20terms%20and%20references%20for%20the%20committee%20is%20%E2%80%9Cexamine%20and%20recommend%E2%80%9D%20if%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20states%20is%20required%20at%20all%20for%20the%20decision%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20for%20Delhi%20and%20states%2C%20which%20has%20a%20direct%20bearing%20on%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20section%20(b)%20of%20%E2%80%98Terms%20and%20References%E2%80%99%20reads%2C%20it%20will%20also%20%E2%80%9Cexamine%20and%20recommend%2C%20if%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20Constitution%20would%20require%20ratification%20by%20the%20States.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20committee%20and%20Adhir%E2%80%99s%20refusal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFormer%20President%20of%20India%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20was%20appointed%20as%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee.%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20Congress%20MP%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20former%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20and%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%2C%20former%20finance%20commission%20chairman%20N.K.%20Singh%2C%20former%20secretary%20general%20Lok%20Sabha%20Subhash%20C.%20Kashyap%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Harish%20Salve%20and%20former%20chief%20vigilance%20commissioner%20Sanjay%20Kothari%20are%20the%20other%20members.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20composition%20of%20the%20committee%20could%20raise%20eyebrows%20as%20almost%20all%20its%20members%20except%20Congress%20Parliamentary%20Party%20leader%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20are%20either%20BJP%20members%20or%20people%20who%20have%20been%20working%20with%20or%20have%20previously%20worked%20with%20the%20Modi%20government.%20Leaders%20of%20regional%20parties%2C%20who%20may%20be%20the%20most%20affected%20by%20simultaneous%20polls%2C%20have%20also%20been%20ignored.%20Former%20and%20current%20election%20commissioners%2C%20who%20may%20be%20the%20best%20placed%20to%20point%20out%20logistical%20problems%20with%20simultaneous%20polls%2C%20also%20do%20not%20figure%20in%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHours%20after%20the%20notification%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20declined%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%208-member%20committee%2C%20writing%20to%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20saying%20he%20was%20of%20the%20view%20the%20exercise%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctotal%20eyewash.%E2%80%9D%20He%20wrote%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cterms%20of%20reference%20have%20been%20prepared%20in%20a%20manner%20to%20guarantee%20its%20conclusions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20termed%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Csudden%20attempt%20to%20thrust%20a%20constitutionally%20suspect%2C%20pragmatically%20non-feasible%20and%20logically%20unimplementable%20idea%20on%20the%20nation%2C%20months%20before%20the%20general%20election%2C%20raising%20serious%20concerns%20about%20the%20ulterior%20motives%20of%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%20He%20said%20he%20found%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20exclusion%20of%20the%20current%20LoP%20from%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20%5BCongress%20President%2C%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%5D%20a%20deliberate%20insult%20to%20the%20system%20of%20Parliamentary%20Democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%E2%80%99s%20K.C.%20Venugopal%20has%20posted%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20noting%20that%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20former%20Congress%20Rajya%20Sabha%20leader%20of%20opposition%2C%20Ghulam%20Nadi%20Azad%20instead%20of%20the%20current%20Congress%20Rajya%20Sabha%20leader%20of%20opposition%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Csystematic%20attempt%20to%20sabotage%20India%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWe%20believe%20that%20the%20High%20Level%20Committee%20on%20Simultaneous%20Elections%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20systematic%20attempt%20to%20sabotage%20India's%20parliamentary%20democracy.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20shocking%20insult%20to%20Parliament%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20appointed%20a%20former%20LOP%20to%20the%20Committee%20instead%20of%20Rajya%20Sabha%20LOP%20Sh.%20Mallikarjun%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20K%20C%20Venugopal%20(%40kcvenugopalmp)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkcvenugopalmp%2Fstatus%2F1697998930665943162%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%202%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20high-level%20committee%20will%20examine%20and%20make%20recommendations%20for%20holding%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20municipalities%20and%20panchayats%2C%20keeping%20in%20view%20the%20existing%20framework%20under%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20and%20other%20statutory%20provisions%2C%20and%20for%20that%20purpose%2C%20examine%20and%20recommend%20specific%20amendments%20to%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201950%2C%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%20and%20the%20rules%20made%20thereunder%20and%20any%20other%20law%20or%20rules%20which%20would%20require%20amendments%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20holding%20simultaneous%20elections%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20is%20expected%20to%20will%20analyse%20and%20recommend%20possible%20solutions%20if%20there%20are%20scenarios%20like%20a%20hung%20house%2C%20adoption%20of%20no-confidence%20motion%20or%20defection.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20will%20examine%20the%20logistics%20and%20manpower%20required%2C%20including%20EVMs%2C%20VVPATs%2C%20etc%2C%20for%20holding%20such%20simultaneous%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20the%20notification.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20notification%20also%20says%20that%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20will%20attend%20the%20committee%20meetings%20as%20a%20special%20invitee.%20The%20committee%20is%20expected%20to%20begin%20functioning%20immediately%20and%20submit%20its%20recommendations%20%E2%80%9Cat%20the%20earliest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObservers%20have%20wondered%20on%20the%20appropriateness%20of%20the%20law%20ministry%20notifying%20this%20with%20Amit%20Shah%20finding%20a%20place%20on%20the%20committee%2C%20with%20Meghwal%20only%20present%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cspecial%20invitee.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20record%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20record%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20government%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20federal%20structure%20is%20questionable%2C%20with%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20happening%20with%20the%20parliament%20arrogating%20to%20itself%20the%20powers%20vested%20in%20the%20(then%20dissolved)%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20state%20assembly.%20In%20an%20unprecedented%20move%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%20a%20state%20was%20bifurcated%20and%20demoted%20to%20a%20Union%20Territory%20without%20its%20views%20being%20taken%20into%20account.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20Delhi%2C%20the%20recent%20Monsoon%20Session%20of%20the%20parliament%20witnessed%20storms%20after%20the%20government%20tabled%20a%20Bill%20in%20parliament%20for%20control%20of%20services%20and%20officers%E2%80%99%20posting%20in%20Delhi%2C%20with%20most%20of%20the%20opposition%20parties%20against%20the%20Bill.%20This%2C%20despite%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20making%20clear%20its%20views%20on%20the%20Ordinance%20brought%20by%20the%20union%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2FImages%2Fpdf1%2FPart20.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArticle%20368(2)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20deals%20with%20amendments%20to%20the%20constitution%2C%20needing%20ratification%20by%20states.%20It%20reads%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CProvided%20that%20if%20such%20amendment%20seeks%20to%20make%20any%20change%20in%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(a)%20article%2054%2C%20article%2055%2C%20article%2073%2C%20article%20162%20or%20article%20241%2C%20or%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(b)%20Chapter%20IV%20of%20Part%20V%2C%20Chapter%20V%20of%20Part%20VI%2C%20or%20Chapter%20I%20of%20Part%20XI%2C%20or%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(c)%20any%20of%20the%20Lists%20in%20the%20Seventh%20Schedule%2C%20or%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(d)%20the%20representation%20of%20States%20in%20Parliament%2C%20or%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(e)%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20article%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20amendment%20shall%20also%20require%20to%20be%20ratified%20by%20the%20Legislatures%20of%20not%20less%20than%20one-half%20of%20the%20States%20by%20resolutions%20to%20that%20effect%20passed%20by%20those%20Legislatures%20before%20the%20Bill%20making%20provision%20for%20such%20amendment%20is%20presented%20to%20the%20President%20for%20assent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20article%20has%20been%20updated%20since%20publication%20with%20news%20on%20Adhir%20Chowdhury%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20be%20on%20it.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693670669000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F25204736%2FScreen-Shot-2020-01-25-at-8.47.13-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcommittee-on-simultaneous-polls%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20controversial%20proposal%20in%20the%20terms%20and%20references%20would%20be%20apiece%20with%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20dismal%20track%20record%20on%20federalism%20or%20even%20just%20for%20consultation%20with%20the%20states.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcommittee-on-simultaneous-polls%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98One%20Piece%E2%80%99%20Showrunner%20Breaks%20Down%20Biggest%20Changes%20Made%20From%20Manga%20That%20Will%20Be%20%E2%80%98Debated%20Endlessly%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693670400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FOP_01225409.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235705985%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22SPOILER%20ALERT%3A%C2%A0This%20interview%20contains%20spoilers%20through%20the%20Season%201%20finale%20of%20%E2%80%9COne%20Piece%2C%E2%80%9D%20now%20streaming%20on%20Netflix.%20Netflix%E2%80%99s%20live-action%20adaptation%20of%20Eiichiro%20Oda%E2%80%99s%20bestselling%20manga%20%E2%80%9COne%20Piece%E2%80%9D%20launched%20Friday%2C%20giving%20fans%20their%20long-awaited%20chance%20to%20compare%20the%20eight-episode%20first%20season%20to%20its%20print%20and%20anime%20versions.%20The%20manga%20takes%20place%20in%20a%20fantastical%20world%20where%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Jennifer%20Maas%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fone-piece-manga-live-action-changes-arlong-don-krieg-1235705985%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fone-piece-manga-live-action-changes-arlong-don-krieg-1235705985%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fone-piece-manga-live-action-changes-arlong-don-krieg-1235705985%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ameesha%20reveals%20Kareena%20was%20thrown%20out%20of%20KNPH%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22pu