(Hosted%20by%20DocumentCloud)%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22540%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuberville's%20disclosure%20shows%20he%20has%20part%20of%20his%20wealth%20spread%20across%20two%20bank%20accounts%20that%20he%20solely%20owns%20and%20six%20that%20he%20shares%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20Suzanne%2C%20amounting%20to%20at%20least%20%24715%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20over%20the%20time%20frame%20covered%20by%20the%20disclosure%2C%20Tuberville%20owned%20two%20pieces%20of%20real%20estate%20with%20his%20wife%3A%20A%20property%20he%20classified%20as%20%26quot%3Bunimproved%20land%26quot%3B%20worth%20at%20least%20%24100%2C001%20in%20Dadeville%2C%20Alabama%2C%20and%20a%20condominium%20in%20Florida%20valued%20at%20%24500%2C001%20at%20minimum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20recent%20Washington%20Post%20report%2C%20Tuberville%20has%20sold%20his%20land%20in%20Alabama%20for%20close%20to%20%241.1%20million%20and%20the%20condo%20for%20%24850%2C000.%20In%20its%20place%2C%20he%20reportedly%20bought%20a%20replacement%20condo%20for%20%24825%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuberville%20and%20his%20wife%20are%20also%20prolific%20stock%20traders%20%E2%80%94%20they%20collectively%20reported%20having%20more%20than%20%243.4%20million%20invested%20in%20various%20stocks%20and%20options%20including%20more%20than%20%24500%2C000%20in%20shares%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Steel%20Corporation%20and%20more%20than%20%24600%2C000%20in%20Apple.%20They%20also%20reported%20having%20more%20than%20%24750%2C000%20invested%20in%20mutual%20funds%20and%20ETFs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disclosure%20also%20notes%20that%20Tuberville%20owned%20several%20futures%20contracts%20in%20soybeans%2C%20cattle%2C%20and%20corn%20while%20simultaneously%20sitting%20on%20the%20Senate%20Committee%20on%20Agriculture%2C%20Nutrition%2C%20and%20Forestry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20his%20reported%20investments%2C%20Tuberville's%20press%20secretary%20told%20Insider%20that%20he%20has%20financial%20advisors%20do%20his%20day-to-day%20trading%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Insider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawmakers-bought-sold-covid-19-related-stocks-during-pandemic-2021-12%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%2C%20Tuberville%20holds%20investments%20in%20several%20companies%20that%20produce%20COVID-19%20tests%2C%20treatments%2C%20and%20vaccines%3A%20Pfizer%2C%20Johnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%2C%20and%203M.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20Tuberville's%20plethora%20of%20investments%2C%20he%20reported%20that%20he%20receives%20a%20monthly%20pension%20stipend%20from%20the%20state%20of%20Alabama%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20in%202022%2C%20he%20received%20a%20total%20of%20%2443%2C246%20from%20it%20%E2%80%94%20in%20addition%20to%20a%20pension%20plan%20that%20has%20yet%20to%20begin%20paying%20out%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Miami.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20not%20listed%20on%20his%20financial%20disclosure%2C%20Tuberville%20earns%20%24174%2C000%20each%20year%20from%20the%20government%20as%20a%20current%20US%20Senator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20after%20the%20now-controversial%20movie's%20release%2C%20Tuberville%20reportedly%20still%20has%20a%20royalty%20agreement%20in%20place%20with%20Warner%20Bros.%20stemming%20from%20his%20brief%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsen-tommy-tuberville-is-still-earning-royalties-from-the-blind-side-2023-8%5C%22%3Ecameo%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Blind%20Side.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20his%20reported%20liabilities%2C%20the%2068-year-old%20isn't%20one%20of%20the%20handful%20of%20members%20of%20Congress%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmembers-of-congress-with-student-loan-debt-2022-3%5C%22%3Estudent%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20did%20report%20that%20he's%20still%20paying%20off%20two%20mortgages%20that%20are%20collectively%20worth%20at%20least%20%241%20million.%20He%20also%20reported%20a%20%26quot%3Brevolving%20charge%26quot%3B%20connected%20to%20his%20American%20Express%20account%20estimated%20at%20at%20least%20%2410%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaking%20the%20most%20of%20his%20short%20time%20in%20office%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Tuberville%20was%20elected%20to%20represent%20Alabama%20in%20the%20US%20Senate%20after%20trouncing%20Trump's%20former%20attorney%20general%2C%20Jeff%20Sessions%2C%20in%20the%20state's%20GOP%20primary%20election%20runoff%20and%20then%20incumbent%20Sen.%20Doug%20Jones%20in%20the%20general%20election.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20taking%20office%20in%202021%2C%20Tuberville's%20sat%20on%20several%20committees%2C%20including%20the%20Senate%20Armed%20Services%20Committee%20and%20the%20Committee%20on%20Agriculture%2C%20Nutrition%2C%20and%20Forestry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20months%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20overturned%20decades%20of%20precedent%20regarding%20abortion%20access%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20announced%20a%20plan%20to%20reimburse%20service%20members%20who%20travel%20out%20of%20state%20for%20abortion%20services.%20In%20response%2C%20Tuberville%20said%20he'd%20use%20his%20power%20to%20prevent%20military%20nominations%20and%20promotions%20from%20passing%20through%20the%20Senate%20until%20the%20policy%20is%20reversed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20Tuberville%20has%20singlehandedly%20blocked%20more%20than%20300%20promotions%20from%20passing%20through%20the%20Senate%20via%20a%20%26quot%3Bunanimous%20consent%26quot%3B%20process%2C%20leaving%20three%20branches%20of%20the%20military%20currently%20without%20a%20Senate-confirmed%20leader%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tuberville.senate.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Ftuberville-op-ed-in-the-washington-times-standing-up-on-abortion-to-most-politicized-pentagon-in-american-history%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%2520February%252016%252C%25202023%252C%2520Secretary%2Ctheir%2520dependents%2520seeking%2520an%2520abortion.%5C%22%3E