ble%20data%2C%20I've%20always%20felt%20like%2090%25%20of%20managers%20found%20themselves%20working%20in%20management%20by%20accident%2C%205%25%20were%20power-hungry%20and%20wanted%20control%20over%20others%2C%20and%205%25%20had%20a%20strong%20desire%20to%20truly%20elevate%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20to%20say%20that%20the%20managers%20who%20found%20themselves%20working%20as%20manager%20by%20accident%20or%20as%20the%20next%20step%20in%20their%20career%20are%20bad%20managers.%20But%20if%20leadership%20isn't%20something%20that%20they%20have%20passion%20for%2C%20we're%20already%20on%20unstable%20ground%20before%20the%20work%20even%20starts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Too%20many%20focus%20on%20actually%20managing%20instead%20of%20leading%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20company%20employs%20managers%20and%20almost%20every%20manager%20working%20today%20has%20a%20job%20title%20with%20%3Cem%3Emanager%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20huge%20disconnect%20from%20what%20individuals%20and%20companies%20say%20that%20they%20want%2C%20which%20is%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20should%20be%20lead%20and%20process%20should%20be%20managed.%20By%20calling%20someone%20a%20manager%20instead%20of%20a%20leader%2C%20the%20implied%20focus%20is%20on%20managing%20%E2%80%94%20which%20usually%20spills%20over%20to%20managing%20people%20instead%20of%20leading%20people.%20This%20issue%20is%20so%20pervasive%20that%20it%20goes%20without%20notice%20in%20all%20our%20lives%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20managers%20will%20describe%20their%20job%20as%20managing%20a%20team%20and%20a%20few%20managers%20will%20describe%20their%20job%20as%20leading%20a%20team.%20when%20discussing%20the%20details%20of%20their%20job%2C%20almost%20all%20managers%20will%20talk%20about%20the%20specifics%20of%20what%20projects%20and%20tasks%20they%20and%20their%20team%20work%20on.%20Very%20few%20managers%20will%20describe%20the%20specifics%20of%20their%20job%20as%20%26quot%3Bleading%20and%20elevating%20others%2C%20who%20accomplish%20tasks.%26quot%3B%20The%20primary%20focus%20is%20on%20what%20they%20do%20instead%20of%20how%20they%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20you%20perform%20your%20job%20in%20a%20managerial%20role%20is%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20other%20people.%20But%20the%20everyday%20words%20used%20by%20managers%20frequently%20fail%20to%20place%20the%20appropriate%20amount%20of%20attention%20to%20the%20real%20duties%20of%20the%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Pressure%20to%20deliver%20can%20push%20manager%20into%20sacrificing%20employee%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20manager%2C%20you're%20required%20to%20manage%20processes%20and%20you're%20expected%20to%20lead%20people.%20Note%20that%20I'm%20using%20these%20words%20deliberately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20witnessed%20plenty%20of%20managers%20that%20managed%20processes%20and%20financial%20performance%20of%20business%20units%20very%20well%20but%20were%20terrible%20people%20leaders.%20However%2C%20because%20of%20the%20ease%20of%20measuring%20business%20results%20and%20the%20focus%20on%20profitability%2C%20companies%20are%20more%20willing%20to%20overlook%20poor%20people%20leadership%20compared%20with%20poor%20business%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20this%20translates%20into%20is%20an%20over-indexing%20on%20delivering%20results%2C%20many%20times%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20real%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20as%20a%20manager%2C%20there's%20a%20constant%20pressure%20to%20deliver%20results%20and%20please%20your%20manager.%20This%20means%20that%20when%20important%20projects%2C%20urgent%20tasks%20from%20executives%2C%20and%20risky%20situations%20arise%2C%20the%20focus%20tends%20to%20shift%20to%20management%20mode%20instead%20of%20leadership%20mode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20situations%2C%20a%20manager%20will%20take%20on%20those%20critical%20tasks%20themselves%20because%20there%20is%20greater%20assurance%20that%20the%20task%20will%20be%20done%20correctly.%20But%20while%20doing%20this%20work%20themselves%20can%20reduce%20inaccuracies%20and%20slow%20processes%2C%20other%20team%20members%20are%20being%20stripped%20of%20opportunities%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20puts%20managers%20between%20a%20rock%20and%20a%20hard%20place%20when%20dealing%20with%20important%20and%20risky%20tasks%2C%20which%20are%20frequently%20the%20same%20tasks%20that%20create%20situations%20required%20for%20others%20to%20grow%20in%20their%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20career%20I%20found%20this%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20challenging%20parts%20of%20being%20a%20leader.%20With%20constant%20pressure%20from%20my%20leaders%2C%20my%20initial%20reaction%20was%20to%20dive%20in%20and%20solve%20an%20urgent%20problem%20just%20as%20I%20had%20done%20as%20an%20individual%20contributor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20a%20people%20leader%2C%20this%20took%20away%20opportunities%20from%20my%20team.%20Over%20time%2C%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20manage%20my%20leaders'%20expectations%20and%20accept%20that%20mistakes%20might%20happen.%20Because%20without%20the%20chance%20to%20make%20mistakes%2C%20team%20members%20wouldn't%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo%20create%20great%20leaders%2C%20we%20need%20to%20change%20the%20way%20that%20we%20think%20about%20management%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20should%20change%20the%20words%20that%20we%20use%20to%20describe%20the%20duties%20of%20the%20role%2C%20and%20the%20expectations%20of%20the%20role.%20We%20also%20need%20to%20re-think%20the%20balance%20of%20risks%20and%20results%2C%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20lost%20opportunities%20for%20team%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20develop%20great%20leaders%2C%20we%20must%20ensure%20that%20team%20members%20understand%20what%20true%20leadership%20is%20about.%20Then%20we%20need%20to%20create%20an%20environment%20the%20fosters%20the%20development%20of%20others%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20opportunities.%3Cbr%3E%