%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E5.2%20billion%20gallons%20of%20water%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%2C%20up%2020%25%20from%20a%20year%20earlier.%20Meta's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-llama2-ai-uses-almost-twice-water-as-llama-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELlama%202%3C%2Fa%3E%20model%20is%20thirsty%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMajor%20players%20in%20the%20race%20for%20AI%20tout%20how%20they%20are%20offsetting%20this%20increased%20environmental%20burden%20with%20programs%20such%20as%20Microsoft's%20commitment%20for%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fazure.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fblog%2Fexpanding-cloud-services-microsoft-launches-its-sustainable-datacenter-region-in-arizona%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMicrosoft%2527s%2520Arizona%2520datacenters%2520will%2520use%2Care%2520below%252085%2520degrees%2520Fahrenheit.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EArizona%20data%20centers%20to%20use%20no%20water%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20year.%20Or%2C%20Google%2C%20which%20recently%20announced%20a%20partnership%20with%20AI%20chip%20giant%20Nvidia%2C%20and%20aims%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsustainability.google%2Foperating-sustainably%2Fwater-stewardship%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dfreshwater%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereplenish%20120%25%20of%20the%20freshwater%20their%20offices%20and%20data%20centers%20use%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20efforts%20may%20be%20mostly%20clever%20marketing%2C%20according%20to%20Adrienne%20Russell%2C%20co-director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Journalism%2C%20Media%2C%20and%20Democracy%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20has%20been%20this%20long%20and%20concerted%20effort%20by%20the%20tech%20industry%20to%20make%20digital%20innovation%20seem%20compatible%20with%20sustainability%20and%20it's%20just%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20cited%20the%20shift%20to%