nt%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fzeenat-aman-recalls-being-described-as-out-of-sync-cursed-and-shattered-in-an-old-film-magazines-see-post%2Farticleshow%2F103307227.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Govt%20Must%20Say%20'Enough%20Is%20Enough'%20and%20Put%20a%20Stop%20to%20Recurring%20Incidents%20of%20Hate%20Speech%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F14154412%2Fhate-speech.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EAn%20abridged%20version%20of%20Justice%20Madan%20B.%20Lokur%20and%20Shruti%20Narayan%E2%80%99s%20chapter%20in%20the%20anthology%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.toaep.org%2Fps-pdf%2F41-bergsmo-manocha%2F%5C%22%3EReligion%2C%20Hateful%20Expression%20and%20Violence%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eis%20published%20here%20with%20the%20permission%20of%20the%20Torkel%20Opsahl%20Academic%20EPublisher%20(TOAEP).%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJafar%20Imam%20Naqvi%20v.%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20issue%20of%20political%20hate%20speech%20re-entered%20the%20discourse%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20during%20the%202014%20parliamentary%20elections.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20petitioner%20sought%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Einter%20alia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20should%20be%20directed%20to%20derecognize%20political%20parties%20resorting%20to%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%E2%80%9D%20activities%2C%20referring%20to%20speeches%20stoking%20religious%20tensions.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20ignored%20the%20specific%20plea%20made%20by%20the%20petitioner%2C%20and%20instead%20mainly%20focused%20on%20reasons%20why%20it%20should%20not%20enter%20the%20legislative%20field%20and%20issue%20%E2%80%9Cguidelines%E2%80%9D.%20Despite%20the%20clear%20danger%20that%20hate%20speech%20presents%2C%20the%20Court%20essentially%20abandoned%20the%20issue%20as%20one%20that%20should%20only%20be%20dealt%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epost%20facto%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Estating%20that%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20matter%20of%20handling%20hate%20speeches%20could%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20adjudication%20in%20an%20appropriate%20legal%20forum%20and%20may%20also%20have%20some%20impact%20in%20an%20election%20dispute%20raised%20under%20the%20Representation%20of%20People%20Act%2C%201951.%20Therefore%2C%20to%20entertain%20a%20petition%20as%20a%20public%20interest%20litigation%20and%20to%20give%20directions%20would%20be%20inappropriate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Court%20unfortunately%20missed%20an%20opportunity%20to%20lay%20down%20the%20limits%20of%20hate%20speech%20which%20gets%20aggravated%20during%20electioneering.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20most%20recent%20judgment%20considering%20the%20issue%20of%20hate%20speech%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmish%20Devgan%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmish%20Devgan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99).%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EDevgan%2C%20a%20television%20journalist%2C%20faced%20criminal%20charges%20under%20various%20provisions%20of%20the%20IPC.%20The%20charges%20were%20filed%20after%20he%20referred%20to%20a%20saint%20in%20Isl%C3%A1m%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinvader%2C%20terrorist%20and%20robber%20who%20had%20come%20to%20India%20to%20convert%20its%20population%20to%20Islam%E2%80%9D%2C%20during%20a%20TV%20programme%20hosted%20by%20him.%20The%20Court%20refused%20to%20quash%20the%20criminal%20cases%2C%20which%20is%20an%20affirmation%20of%20the%20adequacy%20of%20existing%20criminal%20law%20to%20recognize%20hate%20speech%2C%20even%20if%20made%20accidentally%20or%20in%20error%2C%20as%20was%20claimed%20by%20Devgan.%20In%20its%20rather%20lengthy%20judgment%2C%20the%20Court%20embarked%20on%20a%20comprehensive%20review%20of%20Indian%20and%20foreign%20decisions%20on%20hate%20speech%20while%20referring%20to%20some%20helpful%20academic%20articles.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Court%20referred%20to%20the%20guaranteed%20right%20to%20equality%20in%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20its%20various%20facets%2C%20including%20the%20right%20to%20dignity.%20The%20Indian%20Constitution%20prescribes%20not%20just%20rights%20but%20also%20duties%2C%20including%20the%20duty%20of%20citizens%20to%20promote%20harmony%20and%20fraternity%2C%20which%20the%20Court%20noted%20must%20transcend%20%E2%80%9Creligious%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20diversities%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Court%20distinguished%20between%20dignity%20which%20can%20be%20protected%20by%20criminalizing%20hate%20speech%20and%20a%20broader%20or%20more%20individualistic%20concept%20of%20dignity%2C%20which%20is%20protected%20by%20defamation%20law.%20In%20the%20former%20context%2C%20the%20Court%20held%20dignity%20as%20meaning%20%E2%80%9Ca%20person%E2%80%99s%20basic%20entitlement%20as%20a%20member%20of%20a%20society%20in%20good%20standing%2C%20his%20status%20as%20a%20social%20equal%2C%20and%20as%20bearer%20of%20human%20rights%20and%20constitutional%20entitlements%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Court%20accorded%20dignity%20great%20importance%2C%20as%20being%20linked%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunity%20and%20integrity%20of%20the%20nation%E2%80%9D%20and%20held%20that%20divisiveness%20and%20alienation%20affects%20not%20only%20the%20dignity%20of%20the%20target%20group%20but%20also%20the%20pluralism%20and%20diversity%20of%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F21013004%2FIMG_3491.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Credit%3A%20The%20Wire%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F21013004%2FIMG_3491.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F21013004%2FIMG_3491-300x189.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-251444%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22404%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Photo%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20discussing%20various%20subjective%20factors%20necessitating%20evaluation%20for%20deciding%20whether%20speech%20is%20punishable%20as%20hate%20speech%2C%20the%20Court%20referred%20to%20academic%20articles%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20including%20an%20essay%20titled%20%E2%80%98Defining%20Hate%20Speech%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ewhich%20deals%20with%20hate%20speech%20in%20various%20jurisdictions.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20broadly%20accepted%20that%20the%20content%20of%20a%20speech%20must%20be%20coupled%20with%20the%20intent%20of%20the%20speaker%20to%20incite%20or%20cause%20harm.%20The%20Court%20also%20referred%20to%20an%20article%20which%20outlined%20the%20three%20elements%20of%20hate%20speech%20%E2%80%93%20content%2C%20intent%2C%20and%20harm%20or%20impact.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20problem%2C%20in%20the%20authors%E2%80%99%20opinion%2C%20is%20the%20unsatisfactory%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20Court%20dealt%20with%20the%20harm%20or%20impact%20that%20hate%20speech%20might%20have.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20content%20aspect%2C%20the%20Court%20accepted%20an%20earlier%20view%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20effect%20of%20the%20words%20must%20be%20judged%20from%20the%20standards%20of%20reasonable%2C%20strong-minded%2C%20firm%20and%20courageous%20men%2C%20and%20not%20those%20of%20weak%20and%20vacillating%20minds%2C%20nor%20of%20those%20who%20scent%20danger%20in%20every%20hostile%20point%20of%20view%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20intent%20aspect%2C%20the%20Court%20accepted%20the%20view%20that%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20intent-based%20element%20of%20%E2%80%98hate%20speech%E2%80%99%20requires%20the%20speaker%E2%80%99s%20message%20to%20intend%20only%20to%20promote%20hatred%2C%20violence%20or%20resentment%20against%20a%20particular%20class%20or%20group%20without%20communicating%20any%20legitimate%20message.%20This%20requires%20subjective%20intent%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20speaker%20to%20target%20the%20group%20or%20person%20associated%20with%20the%20class%2Fgroup.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20also%20cited%20various%20definitions%20not%20previously%20considered%20by%20it%20or%20by%20the%20Law%20Commission.%20One%20of%20the%20definitions%20views%20hate%20speech%20as%20a%20racial%20insult%20intended%20to%20demean%20a%20group%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ewhile%20another%20explains%20it%20as%20expression%20intended%20to%20%E2%80%9Cvilify%2C%20humiliate%20or%20incite%20hatred%E2%80%9D%20against%20a%20target.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Court%20also%20affirmed%20that%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech%20may%20not%20be%20arbitrarily%20restrained%20by%20hate%20speech%20laws.%20The%20Court%20opined%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%E2%80%98good%20faith%E2%80%99%20defence%20available%20where%20a%20speaker%20displays%20prudence%20and%20caution%20with%20his%20or%20her%20expression%20or%20content%3B%20and%20that%20there%20is%20also%20a%20%E2%80%98legitimate%20purpose%E2%80%99%20defence%20available%20where%20the%20speech%20has%20some%20clear%20purpose%20other%20than%20just%20spreading%20hatred%20or%20intent.%20This%20is%20a%20corollary%20to%20the%20definition%20of%20hate%20speech%20in%20Black%E2%80%99s%20Law%20Dictionary%2C%20which%20views%20hate%20speech%20as%20speech%20with%20no%20redeeming%20purpose%20other%20than%20spreading%20hatred.%20The%20Court%20held%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Clegitimate%20purpose%E2%80%9D%20defence%20is%20particularly%20applicable%20in%20cases%20of%20any%20publication%20having%20a%20genuine%20public%20interest%20purpose.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHate%20Speech%20and%20Fair%20Criticism%20of%20Government%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmish%20Devgan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Court%20sought%20to%20clarify%20the%20law%20on%20restraining%20free%20speech%20by%20holding%20that%20speech%20which%20threatens%20the%20security%20of%20the%20State%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20speech%20prohibited%20by%20other%20provisions%20of%20the%20IPC.%20Even%20within%20the%20context%20of%20speech%20relating%20to%20government%20and%20public%20administration%2C%20the%20Court%20reaffirmed%20that%20the%20right%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfavour%20or%20criticise%E2%80%9D%20government%20policies%20is%20within%20the%20right%20to%20free%20speech%2C%20and%20such%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20speech%E2%80%9D%20does%20not%20constitute%20hate%20speech.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20present%20context%2C%20this%20is%20an%20important%20distinction%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20understood%20by%20the%20police.%20The%20misuse%20of%20these%20provisions%20of%20law%20to%20target%20people%20making%20political%20comments%20is%20illustrated%20in%20the%20case%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPatricia%20Mukhim%20v.%20State%20of%20Meghalaya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20case%20was%20decided%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%2025%20March%2C%202021%2C%20just%20over%20three%20months%20after%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20judgment%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmish%20Devgan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Mukhim%20is%20a%20journalist%20in%20the%20north-eastern%20State%20of%20Meghalaya%2C%20where%20conflicts%20sometimes%20occur%20between%20tribal%20and%20non-tribal%20communities.%20In%20July%202020%2C%20Mukhim%20wrote%20a%20Facebook%20post%20criticizing%20the%20%E2%80%9Capathy%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20State%20government%20functionaries%20in%20not%20taking%20any%20action%20in%20relation%20to%20an%20incident%20where%20certain%20persons%20attacked%20non-tribals.%20She%20was%20charged%20in%20a%20criminal%20case%20accusing%20her%20of%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20groups%20on%20grounds%20of%20religion%20and%20race%20as%20well%20as%20promoting%20hatred%20or%20ill-will.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20quashed%20the%20criminal%20case%20against%20Mukhim.%20In%20its%20judgment%2C%20it%20held%20that%20the%20Facebook%20post%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20%E2%80%9Chighlight%20the%20discrimination%20against%20non-tribals%20in%20the%20State%20of%20Meghalaya%E2%80%9D%20and%20in%20fact%20%E2%80%9Cpleads%20for%20equality%20of%20non-tribals%20in%20the%20State%20of%20Meghalaya%E2%80%9D.%20There%20was%20no%20discernible%20intent%20to%20promote%20hatred%20of%20any%20community.%20The%20Court%20went%20on%20to%20note%20that%20within%20India%E2%80%99s%20multi-cultural%20society%2C%20where%20citizens%20enjoy%20the%20right%20to%20free%20movement%20within%20the%20country%2C%20there%20is%20potential%20for%20conflict%20which%20cannot%20be%20ignored.%20The%20Court%20held%20that%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fervent%20plea%20made%20by%20the%20Appellant%20for%20protection%20of%20non-tribals%20living%20in%20the%20State%20of%20Meghalaya%20and%20for%20their%20equality%20cannot%2C%20by%20any%20stretch%20of%20imagination%2C%20be%20categorized%20as%20hate%20speech.%20It%20was%20a%20call%20for%20justice%20%E2%80%93%20for%20action%20according%20to%20law%2C%20which%20every%20citizen%20has%20a%20right%20to%20expect%20and%20articulate.%20Disapprobation%20of%20governmental%20inaction%20cannot%20be%20branded%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20promote%20hatred%20between%20different%20communities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F11202501%2FScreen-Shot-2020-07-11-at-8.24.38-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22861%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F11202501%2FScreen-Shot-2020-07-11-at-8.24.38-PM.png%20861w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F11202501%2FScreen-Shot-2020-07-11-at-8.24.38-PM-300x149.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-466192%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22427%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EShillong%20Times%20editor%C2%A0Patricia%20Mukhim.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDoes%20the%20Impact%20of%20Hate%20Speech%20Need%20to%20Be%20%E2%80%98Violent%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPravasi%20Bhalai%20Sangathan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ehad%20already%20held%20that%20the%20impact%20of%20hate%20speech%20may%20include%20a%20non-violent%20psychological%20impact.%20This%20was%20reiterated%20by%20the%20Law%20Commission.%20However%2C%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmish%20Devgan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Court%20noted%20that%20speech%20which%20goes%20beyond%20political%20criticism%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdefames%2C%20stigmatizes%20and%20insults%20the%20targeted%20group%20provoking%20violence%20or%20psychosocial%20hatred%E2%80%9D%20is%20not%20protected%20free%20speech.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20Court%20elaborated%20that%20speech%20reflecting%20%E2%80%9Chate%20which%20tends%20to%20vilify%2C%20humiliate%20and%20incite%20hatred%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eor%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eviolence%20against%20the%20target%20group%20upon%20identity%20of%20the%20group%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20can%20be%20punished.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20Court%20appears%20to%20be%20veering%20towards%20the%20view%20that%20hate%20speech%20must%20extend%20to%20incitement%20to%20violence%2C%20if%20not%20violence%20itself.%20It%20was%20observed%20that%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20actual%20violence%20or%20public%20disorder%20%E2%80%9Csomething%20more%20than%20words%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%E2%80%98clear%20and%20present%20danger%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98imminent%20lawless%20action%E2%80%99%2C%20either%20by%20the%20maker%20or%20by%20others%20at%20the%20maker%E2%80%99s%20instigation%20is%20required%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%E2%80%98clear%20and%20present%20danger%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98imminent%20lawless%20action%E2%80%99%20tests%20are%20two%20distinct%20tests%20in%20US%20constitutional%20law%2C%20but%20have%20been%20equated%20by%20the%20Indian%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThese%20expressions%20are%20employed%20in%20the%20context%20of%20public%20disorder%20or%20violence%20and%20not%20simply%20in%20the%20context%20of%20promoting%20feelings%20of%20hatred.%20This%20equation%20of%20the%20two%20distinct%20tests%20by%20the%20Indian%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20made%20it%20simple%20for%20the%20Court%20to%20decline%20any%20answer%20to%20the%20question%20as%20to%20whether%2C%20for%20example%2C%20economic%20boycott%20of%20a%20particular%20community%20falls%20within%20the%20meaning%20of%20%E2%80%98clear%20and%20present%20danger%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98imminent%20lawless%20action%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20context%20of%20public%20disorder.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20did%20not%20elaborate%20on%20how%20the%20%E2%80%98clear%20and%20present%20danger%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98imminent%20lawless%20action%E2%80%99%20tests%20may%20be%20applied%20to%20evaluate%20whether%20a%20given%20speech%20would%20promote%20feelings%20of%20hatred%20against%20a%20particular%20community%20without%20extending%20to%20physical%20harm.%20The%20Court%20merely%20accepted%20an%20earlier%20view%20that%20to%20criminalize%20speech%2C%20it%20is%20necessary%20to%20establish%20a%20proximate%20nexus%20with%20clear%20and%20present%20danger%20or%20imminent%20lawless%20action%20and%20public%20disorder%20or%20violence.%20The%20Court%20appears%20to%20recognize%20this%20problem%20but%20does%20not%20provide%20any%20satisfactory%20conclusion%2C%20holding%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20interpreted%20the%20relevant%20provisions%2C%20we%20are%20conscious%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20have%20given%20primacy%20to%20the%20precept%20of%20%E2%80%98interest%20of%20public%20order%E2%80%99%20and%20by%20relying%20upon%20%E2%80%98imminent%20lawless%20action%E2%80%99%20principle%2C%20not%20given%20due%20weightage%20to%20the%20long-term%20impact%20of%20%E2%80%98hate%E2%80%99%20speech%20as%20a%20propaganda%20on%20both%20the%20targeted%20and%20non-targeted%20groups.%20This%20is%20not%20to%20undermine%20the%20concept%20of%20dignity%2C%20which%20is%20the%20fundamental%20foundation%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20which%20the%20citizens%20must%20interact%20between%20themselves%20and%20with%20the%20State.%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D.%20Further%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98hate%20speech%E2%80%99%20meeting%20the%20criteria%20of%20%E2%80%98clear%20and%20present%20danger%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98imminent%20lawless%20action%E2%80%99%20would%20necessarily%20have%20long%20term%20negative%20effect.%20Lastly%2C%20we%20are%20dealing%20with%20penal%20or%20criminal%20action%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20have%20to%20balance%20the%20right%20to%20express%20and%20speak%20with%20retaliatory%20criminal%20proceedings.%20We%20have%20to%20also%20prevent%20abuse%20and%20check%20misuse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20authors%E2%80%99%20opinion%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20taken%20a%20step%20back%20from%20its%20pronouncement%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPravasi%20Bhalai%20Sangathan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Law%20Commission.%20Incitement%20to%20a%20non-violent%20reaction%20to%20hate%20speech%20is%20as%20much%20an%20offence%20as%20any.%20For%20example%2C%20an%20economic%20boycott%20of%20members%20of%20a%20minority%20community%20amounts%20to%20discriminatory%20treatment%20with%20an%20intent%20to%20humiliate%20and%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20punishable%20under%20the%20existing%20legal%20provisions.%20Such%20an%20action%20is%20a%20direct%20manifestation%20of%20feelings%20of%20hate.%20While%20the%20Court%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmish%20Devgan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Edoes%20not%20expressly%20state%20as%20much%2C%20its%20silence%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20taken%20as%20an%20indication%20that%20only%20incitement%20to%20violence%20or%20a%20likelihood%20of%20violence%20will%20matter%20for%20prosecution%20under%20the%20law.%20Such%20an%20interpretation%20would%20go%20against%20the%20hate%20speech%20jurisprudence%20somewhat%20ambiguously%20elucidated%20in%20the%20decision%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmish%20Devgan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eitself.%20To%20avoid%20any%20doubt%20as%20to%20understanding%20speech%20as%20hate%20speech%2C%20it%20may%20be%20preferable%20to%20introduce%20specific%20provisions%20making%20hate%20speech%20an%20offence%20as%20proposed%20by%20the%20Law%20Commission%20in%20its%20Report%20regardless%20of%20the%20harm%20or%20impact%20on%20society%20or%20a%20community%20or%20an%20individual.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPravasi%20Bhalai%20Sangathan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Epointed%20out%20that%20the%20existing%20legal%20provisions%20could%20be%20used%20to%20prosecute%20and%20punish%20hate%20speech%20when%20it%20occurred.%20In%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmish%20Devgan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Court%20refused%20to%20quash%20the%20criminal%20case%20against%20the%20journalist%20accused%20of%20making%20a%20hate%20speech.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20judiciary%20approved%20the%20use%20of%20existing%20law%20to%20prosecute%20hate%20speech.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20upon%20examining%20some%20major%20contemporary%20incidents%20of%20divisive%20and%20hateful%20speech%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20police%20are%20not%20always%20proactive%20in%20investigating%2C%20let%20alone%20prosecuting%2C%20such%20incidents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EContemporary%20incidents%20of%20hate%20speech%2C%20its%20weaponization%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConstitutionally%20guaranteed%20free%20speech%20in%20India%20is%20at%20a%20crossroads.%20It%20must%20be%20appreciated%20that%20hate%20speech%20can%20never%20be%20protected%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20direct%20or%20inferential%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20verbal%20or%20non-verbal.%20Therefore%2C%20a%20clear%20definition%20of%20hate%20speech%20is%20necessary.%20While%20it%20is%20true%20that%20it%20may%20eventually%20be%20difficult%20to%20have%20a%20precise%20definition%20of%20hate%20speech%2C%20a%20beginning%20is%20necessary.%20Time%2C%20it%20is%20said%2C%20is%20a%20great%20healer%20and%20the%20gradual%20passage%20of%20time%20can%20also%20bring%20about%20a%20balance%20in%20the%20definition%20that%20may%20be%20needed%20for%20a%20clearer%20understanding%20of%20the%20distinction%20between%20free%20speech%20and%20hate%20speech.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20has%20accepted%20the%20content%2C%20intent%20and%20impact%20or%20harm%20as%20a%20working%20module%20for%20defining%20hate%20speech.%20This%20must%20be%20carried%20forward%2C%20although%20the%20authors%20believe%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98impact%20or%20harm%E2%80%99%20factor%20as%20understood%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20narrow.%20Hate%20speech%20need%20not%20result%20in%20violence%20or%20a%20possibility%20of%20violence.%20Hate%20speech%20can%20disturb%20the%20mental%20equilibrium%20of%20any%20person%20who%20is%20targeted%20and%20this%20can%20manifest%20itself%20in%20psychosocial%20problems%20and%20trauma.%20These%20are%20not%20visible%20manifestations%20of%20the%20impact%20or%20harm%20caused%20by%20hate%20speech%20but%20are%20nevertheless%20quite%20real%20and%20must%20be%20recognized.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20it%20would%20be%20worth%20exploring%20the%20possibility%20of%20introducing%20the%20theory%20of%20absolute%20liability%20to%20criminalize%20hate%20speech.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20observed%20that%20hate%20speech%20has%20no%20redeeming%20or%20legitimate%20purpose%20other%20than%20hatred%20towards%20a%20particular%20group%20(or%20an%20individual).%20If%20that%20be%20so%2C%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20absolute%20liability%2C%20the%20likelihood%20of%20possibility%20of%20harm%20or%20an%20adverse%20impact%20on%20a%20group%20or%20a%20person%20loses%20its%20relevance.%20As%20long%20as%20the%20content%20test%20and%20the%20intent%20test%20are%20met%2C%20it%20might%20be%20possible%20to%20successfully%20prosecute%20the%20maker%20of%20hate%20speech.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHate%20speech%20in%20India%20is%20resulting%20in%20polarization%20and%20divisiveness.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20clear%20understanding%20on%20what%20constitutes%20hate%20speech%2C%20the%20police%20are%20virtually%20having%20a%20free%20hand%20on%20whom%20to%20prosecute%20and%20to%20let%20off.%20This%20also%20puts%20the%20courts%20in%20a%20quandary%2C%20especially%20in%20matters%20relating%20to%20the%20grant%20of%20discretionary%20bail.%20Unless%20hate%20speech%20is%20checked%20immediately%2C%20its%20impact%20will%20be%20long-term%20and%20dangerous%20to%20society%20and%20perhaps%20the%20country%20itself.%20It%20is%20time%20for%20the%20executive%20arm%20of%20the%20government%20as%20well%20as%20the%20political%20governance%20structures%20to%20display%20sagacity%20and%20shout%20out%20that%20enough%20is%20enough%20and%20put%20a%20stop%20to%20recurring%20incidents%20of%20hate%20speech%2C%20both%20verbal%20as%20well%20as%20non-verbal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20judiciary%20too%20should%20be%20alive%20to%20the%20consequence%20of%20hate%20speech%20not%20being%20punished%20suitably%20and%20in%20time.%20It%20is%20often%20said%20that%20%E2%80%98delay%20defeats%20justice%E2%80%99.%20But%20what%20is%20more%20problematic%20with%20delay%20in%20punishing%20hate%20speech%20is%20not%20that%20justice%20is%20denied%2C%20but%20that%20freedoms%20in%20a%20free%20society%20get%20compromised%20or%20corroded%20to%20the%20detriment%20of%20targeted%20individuals%2C%20groups%20or%20communities.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20appears%20to%20have%20taken%20notice%20of%20the%20urgency%20of%20policing%20hate%20speech.%20In%20a%20petition%20seeking%20redress%20against%20the%20proliferation%20of%20hate%20speech%2C%20the%20Court%20in%20October%202022%20directed%20three%20state%20police%20forces%20to%20take%20immediate%20action%20to%20register%20cases%20against%20any%20incidents%20of%20hate%20speech%20in%20their%20jurisdictions%2C%20%E2%80%9Ceven%20if%20no%20complaint%20is%20forthcoming%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Court%20extended%20its%20order%20to%20all%20states%20in%20April%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%2C%20however%2C%20whether%20state%20authorities%20use%20this%20order%20to%20prosecute%20genuine%20cases%20of%20hate%20speech.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20democracy%20can%20afford%20to%20have%20sections%20of%20society%20lose%20these%20freedoms%20and%20allow%20hate%20to%20take%20over.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20time%20is%20ripe%20for%20India%20to%20introspect%20and%20take%20the%20lead%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20time%20starts%20now.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693646979000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2F14154412%2Fhate-speech.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-hate-speech-violence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20time%20for%20the%20executive%20arm%20of%20the%20government%20as%20well%20as%20the%20political%20governance%20structures%20to%20display%20sagacity%20and%20shout%20out%20that%20enough%20is%20enough%20and%20put%20a%20stop%20to%20recurring%20incidents%20of%20hate%20speech.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-hate-speech-violence%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Scam%202003%20-%20The%20Telgi%20Story'%20Is%20Obsessed%20With%20The%20What%20and%20How%2C%20Rather%20Than%20the%20Why%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02142852%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.26.54-PM_cleanup.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHansal%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20web%20shows%20seem%20riddled%20with%20a%20specific%20set%20of%20contradictions.%20The%20protagonists%20%E2%80%93%20based%20on%20real-life%20figures%20%E2%80%93%20seem%20infused%20with%20a%20larger-than-life%20glow.%20The%20setting%20is%20grounded%20in%20a%20fact-based%20environment%2C%20and%20yet%20characters%20talk%20like%20they%E2%80%99re%20in%20a%20film.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20show%20delves%20into%20the%20nitty-gritty%20of%20the%20world%20just%20enough%20to%20draw%20attention%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98research%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20but%20the%20insights%20are%20mostly%20generic.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20shows%20are%20largely%20well-acted%20and%20have%20flourishes%20of%20%E2%80%9890s%20cinema%2C%20but%20there%20is%20rarely%20anything%20disruptive%2C%20choosing%2C%20instead%2C%20to%20co-opt%20it%20by%20comforting%20nostalgia.%20The%20supporting%20cast%20(thanks%20to%20Mukesh%20Chhabra)%20have%20interesting%20faces%2C%20who%20do%20their%20job%20well%2C%20however%20offer%20just%20one%20characteristic%20for%20their%20parts%3A%20the%20%E2%80%98greedy%E2%80%99%20cop%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98disapproving%E2%80%99%20father-in-law%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98corrupt%E2%80%99%20politician.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20protagonists%20act%20like%20they%E2%80%99re%20already%20living%20and%20breathing%20in%20a%20web%20series.%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20arc%20here%2C%20only%20bullet%20points%20and%20the%20eventual%20destination.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FJrotIxxCXiA%3Fsi%3DnoXfFjXADfUlLIQT%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%2C%20in%20a%20scene%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EScam%202003%3A%20The%20Telgi%20Story%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(on%20Sony%20LIV)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20protagonist%20Abdul%20Karim%20Telgi%20(Gagan%20Dev%20Riar)%20and%20his%20accomplice%2C%20Kaushal%20(Hemang%20Vyas)%20get%20beaten%20by%20their%20competitors%20in%20a%20park%2C%20for%20trying%20to%20source%20revenue%20stamps%20for%20an%20area%20outside%20their%20%E2%80%98jurisdiction%E2%80%99.%20While%20Kaushal%20is%20howling%20in%20pain%2C%20we%20see%20Telgi%20notice%20a%20man%20from%20the%20competitor%E2%80%99s%20gang%20not%20stealing%20the%20revenue%20stamps%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20buy%2C%20but%20the%20stamp%20papers%20they%E2%80%99re%20pasted%20on.%20It%E2%80%99s%20like%20the%20show%20slows%20down%20to%20pointedly%20shine%20a%20light%20on%20Telgi%E2%80%99s%20brilliance%20in%20the%20most%20obvious%20way.%20This%20is%20a%20problem%20in%20Hansal%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20shows%20%E2%80%93%20the%20protagonist%20already%20sees%20something%20others%20don%E2%80%99t.%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20arrive%20at%20it%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20journey%20to%20undertake.%20It%20feels%20like%20a%20filmmaking%20equivalent%20of%20Mehta%20saying%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cthey%E2%80%99re%20built%20differently%E2%80%9D%2C%20rather%20than%20trying%20to%20explore%20what%20makes%20them%20different.%20Is%20it%20their%20less-than-favourable%20circumstances%2C%20or%20just%20their%20pathological%20behaviour%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EScam%202003%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20adapted%20from%20Sanjay%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETelgi%3A%20Ek%20Reporter%20Ki%20Diary%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Edirected%20by%20Tushar%20Hiranandani%20(with%20Hansal%20Mehta%20still%20as%20showrunner)%2C%20traverses%20a%20similar%20path%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EScam%201992%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Sony%20LIV%20has%20released%20the%20first%20five%20episodes%20%E2%80%93%20apparently%20the%20first%20volume%20of%20a%20two-parter.%20Like%20its%20predecessor%2C%20even%20this%20instalment%20seems%20obsessed%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98what%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98how%E2%80%99%2C%20over%20the%20%E2%80%98why%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWritten%20by%20Kiran%20Yagnopavit%2C%20Kedar%20Patankar%20(of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKaun%20Pravin%20Tambe%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fame)%20along%20with%20Karan%20Vyas%20(also%20credited%20for%20the%20dialogues)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20show%20begins%20in%20early%20%E2%80%9880s%20in%20Khanapur%20(Karnataka)%2C%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20introduced%20to%20Abdul%20as%20a%20fruit%20seller%20on%20a%20train.%20A%20stranger%20(Talat%20Aziz)%20recognises%20his%20enterprising%20nature%2C%20and%20ability%20to%20deliver%20silver-tongued%20sales%20pitches%2C%20offering%20him%20to%20come%20work%20in%20Mumbai.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHiranandani%20milks%20the%20beginning%20of%20every%20rags-to-riches%20montage%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20where%20an%20immigrant%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20city%20intoxicated%20with%20the%20promise%20of%20a%20good%20life.%20Phrases%20like%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EBambai%20ki%20hawa%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Bombay%E2%80%99s%20air)%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Esapno%20ki%20nagri%20%3C%2Fem%3E(city%20of%20dreams)%E2%80%9D%20and%20visuals%20of%20worn-out%20sandals%20held%20together%20by%20a%20safety%20pin%20%E2%80%93%20are%20thrown%20at%20the%20viewer.%20A%20good%20example%20of%20reinventing%20the%20trope%20of%20an%20immigrant%E2%80%99s%20worn-out%20sandals%20might%20be%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJubilee%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(2023)%20%E2%80%93%20where%20Atul%20Sabharwal%20uses%20it%20to%20inject%20grace%20and%20warmth%20from%20an%20unforgiving%20city%20in%20the%20most%20unexpected%20moment.%20Which%20is%20exactly%20what%20makes%20Mumbai%20such%20a%20magical%20place%20to%20live%20in.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02143942%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.27.23.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02143942%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.27.23.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02143942%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.27.23-300x158.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02143942%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.27.23-1024x539.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671174%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22632%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20%E2%80%98Scam%202003%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Telgi%20Story%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStarting%20off%20working%20in%20a%20lodge%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20told%20Abdul%20is%20a%20man%20in%20a%20hurry.%20After%20working%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%20for%20about%20seven%20years%2C%20he%20comes%20back%20to%20start%20his%20own%20travel%20agency.%20But%20we%E2%80%99re%20also%20relayed%20in%20the%20first%20scene%20that%20his%20real%20income%20is%20from%20providing%20forged%20documents%20to%20poor%20people%20and%20sending%20them%20to%20work%20abroad.%20Has%20he%20always%20been%20morally%20flexible%20%E2%80%93%20the%20series%20chooses%20not%20to%20dwell%20on%20it.%20When%20did%20he%20cross%20over%20to%20the%20other%20side%3F%20Was%20there%20ever%20fear%2Fdoubt%2Fdesperation%20in%20him%20when%20he%20decided%20to%20do%20this%3F%20What%20prompts%20Telgi%E2%80%99s%20outburst%20at%20a%20later%20stage%2C%20when%20he%20kills%20someone%20who%20betrays%20him%3F%20The%20series%20conveniently%20glides%20over%20his%20head-space.%20How%20did%20a%20humble%20fruit%20seller%2C%20who%20talks%20his%20way%20out%20of%20most%20sticky%20situations%2C%20choose%20violence%3F%20The%20show%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20stop%20to%20wonder.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EScam%202003%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20seems%20like%20a%20checklist-based%20approach%20towards%20filmmaking%20at%20its%20most%20pedantic.%20Linearly%20following%20Telgi%E2%80%99s%20journey%2C%20from%20his%20first%20visit%20to%20jail%2C%20we%20see%20him%20meet%20his%20accomplice%20who%20introduces%20him%20to%20forging%20revenue%20stamps%2C%20thereby%20resulting%20in%20him%20chancing%20upon%20the%20business%20of%20forging%20stamp%20papers.%20Choosing%20between%20the%20abundance%20of%20specific%20details%20to%20tell%20us%20exactly%20how%20the%20scam%20took%20place%20and%20why%20Telgi%20did%20what%20he%20did%20%E2%80%93%20the%20show%20seems%20content%20to%20tackle%20only%20the%20former.%20So%2C%20it%20goes%20into%20granular%20detail%20around%20at%20least%20three%20ways%20to%20counterfeit%20stamp%20paper%20in%20the%20first%20five%20episodes%2C%20mistaking%20jargon%20for%20depth.%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20problem%20Telgi%20can%E2%80%99t%20solve.%20Which%20is%20why%20even%20though%20showrunners%20introduce%20obstacles%20in%20his%20path%2C%20conveying%20how%20he%20was%20playing%20with%20fire%2C%20we%20also%20know%20he%20will%20find%20a%20way.%20Because%20every%20now%20and%20then%20in%20the%20show%2C%20with%20his%20back%20against%20the%20wall%2C%20Telgi%20delivers%20a%20one-liner%20and%20walk%20away%20with%20swagger%20with%20guitars%20from%20the%20main%20theme%20playing%20in%20the%20background.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20baffling%20things%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EScam%202003%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20how%20uncurious%20it%20is%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ewho%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20Abdul%20Karim%20Telgi%3F%20It%20only%20wants%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20exploits%2C%20how%20he%20did%20it%20%E2%80%93%20and%20what%20was%20the%20fallout%20of%20his%20actions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20denying%20that%20the%20show%20is%20well-acted%20though.%20The%20supporting%20cast%20includes%20familiar%20faces%20like%20Nandu%20Madhav%20%E2%80%93%20oscillating%20between%20being%20a%20violent%20cop%20and%20an%20ever-smiling%20ally%2C%20Sameer%20Dharmadhikari%20as%20corrupt%20politician%20Tukaram%2C%20%E2%80%9890s%20popular%20face%20Bhawana%20Balsawar%20playing%20a%20politician%20who%20wears%20pearls%2C%20and%20folds%20her%20hands%20as%20a%20response%20to%20most%20things.%20Marathi%20actor%20Bharat%20Jadhav%20is%20exceptional%20as%20a%20govt%20employee%2C%20who%20mistreats%20Telgi%20as%20a%20small-timer%2C%20only%20to%20turn%20into%20a%20dutiful%2C%20obedient%20child%20when%20the%20tides%20turn.%20There%E2%80%99s%20also%20the%20part%20of%20a%20bar%20dancer%2C%20based%20on%20real-life%20dancer%20Tarannum%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20rumoured%20to%20have%20earned%20crores%20after%20Telgi%20and%20men%20like%20him%20were%20besotted%20by%20her.%20However%2C%20she%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20get%20a%20single%20line%20of%20dialogue%2C%20instead%20simply%20turning%20up%20in%20Madhuri%20Dixit%20outfits%20scene%20after%20scene.%20These%20are%20all%20intriguing%20characters%2C%20performed%20well%2C%20but%20they%E2%80%99re%20all%20terribly%20underwritten.%20They%E2%80%99re%20allowed%20to%20flourish%20only%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20their%20function%20in%20Telgi%E2%80%99s%20grand%20scheme%20of%20things%20within%20the%20show.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02143928%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.27.34.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02143928%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.27.34.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02143928%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.27.34-300x156.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02143928%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-2.27.34-1024x532.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671173%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22624%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20%E2%80%98Scam%202003%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Telgi%20Story%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20focus%20is%20entirely%20on%20Gagan%20Dev%20Riar%E2%80%99s%20Telgi%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20stodgy%20physique%20is%20at%20direct%20odds%20with%20how%20fast%20and%20loose%20his%20brain%20works.%20A%20good%20student%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20behaviour%2C%20the%20show%20somewhat%20explains%20what%20made%20Telgi%20such%20an%20effective%20businessman.%20Showing%20up%20with%20a%20duffle%20bag%20and%20a%20%E2%80%98gift%E2%80%99%20for%20most%20government%20servants%20and%20politicians%2C%20Riar%20brings%20a%20necessary%20sliminess%20to%20Telgi.%20He%20paints%20a%20character%20we%20empathise%20with%2C%20somewhat%20root%20for%2C%20and%20someone%20we%20come%20to%20fear.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Harshad%20Mehta%20and%20Abdul%20Karim%20Telgi%20are%20interesting%20characters%20for%20how%20they%20came%20in%20from%20the%20outside%2C%20found%20ways%20to%20profit%20off%20a%20corrupt%20system%2C%20making%20obscene%20amounts%20of%20money%20for%20everyone%20in%20the%20process.%20However%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20eventually%20thrown%20under%20the%20bus%20by%20a%20significantly%20larger%20system%20that%20continues%20to%20operate%20in%20similarly%20corrupt%20ways.%20So%2C%20then%20are%20they%20criminals%20or%20scapegoats%20of%20a%20larger%20corrupt%20establishment%3F%20By%20putting%20them%20behind%20bars%2C%20are%20we%20curing%20a%20diseased%20society%20or%20simply%20suppressing%20its%20symptoms%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EScam%202003%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20ends%20on%20an%20explosive%20note%20%E2%80%94%20after%20Telgi%20is%20shown%20to%20have%20spent%20Rs%2090%20lakhs%20in%20a%20dance%20bar%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20night.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20rare%20moment%20of%20hubris%20getting%20the%20better%20of%20someone%20who%20liked%20operating%20from%20the%20shadows.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20rare%20moment%20where%20a%20dated%20sequence%20like%20men%20showering%20currency%20on%20bar%20dancers%2C%20gets%20new%20sociological%20context.%20The%20centrepiece%20of%20the%20sequence%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20woman%2C%20but%20men%20trying%20to%20prove%20their%20manliness%20by%20summoning%20trays%20full%20of%20cash.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20petty%2C%20pathetic%20sight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20almost%20wishes%20that%20such%20sharp%20insights%20are%