hewire.in%2Fspace%2Fchandrayaan-3-vikram-lander-successful-soft-landing-moon%5C%22%3Esuccessfully%20soft%20landed%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20on%20August%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20observatory%20was%20launched%20in%20the%20PSLV%20from%20the%20Satish%20Dhawan%20Space%20Centre%20in%20Sriharikota.%20The%20Aditya%20L1%20mission%E2%80%99s%20goal%20is%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20dynamics%20of%20several%20solar%20phenomena%20by%20imaging%20and%20measuring%20particles%20in%20the%20sun%E2%80%99s%20upper%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spacecraft%20carries%20seven%20payloads%20to%20observe%20the%20photosphere%2C%20chromosphere%20and%20the%20outermost%20layers%20of%20the%20Sun%2C%20called%20the%20corona%2C%20using%20electromagnetic%2C%20particle%20and%20magnetic%20field%20detectors.%20Four%20payloads%20will%20directly%20view%20the%20Sun%20and%20the%20remaining%20three%20payloads%20will%20carry%20out%20in-situ%20studies%20of%20particles%20and%20fields%2C%20%E2%80%9Cproviding%20important%20scientific%20studies%20of%20the%20propagatory%20effect%20of%20solar%20dynamics%20in%20the%20interplanetary%20medium%E2%80%9D%2C%20according%20to%20ISRO.%20The%20space%20agency%20plans%20to%20understand%20phenomena%20like%20the%20problem%20of%20coronal%20heating%2C%20coronal%20mass%20ejection%2C%20pre-flare%20and%20flare%20activities%20and%20their%20characteristics%2C%20and%20the%20dynamics%20of%20space%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02120024%2Faditya-payload.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02120024%2Faditya-payload.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02120024%2Faditya-payload-300x130.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671142%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22443%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAditya%20L1%E2%80%99s%20scientific%20payload.%20Photo%3A%20ISRO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02121037%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-12.10.02-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02121037%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-12.10.02-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02121037%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-12.10.02-PM-300x127.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02121037%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-12.10.02-PM-1024x434.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671147%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22509%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20spacecraft%20will%20be%20placed%20in%20a%20low%20earth%20orbit.%20The%20orbit%20is%20gradually%20made%20more%20elliptical%2C%20after%20which%20the%20spacecraft%20will%20be%20launched%20towards%20its%20destination%3A%20L1%20refers%20or%20Lagrange%20point%201%20(L1)%20of%20the%20Sun-Earth%20system%2C%20which%20is%20about%201.5%20million%20km%20from%20the%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELagrange%20points%20are%20positions%20in%20space%20where%20the%20gravitational%20pull%20of%20the%20two%20large%20bodies%20equals%20the%20necessary%20centripetal%20force%20required%20for%20a%20small%20object%20to%20move%20with%20them%20%E2%80%93%20meaning%20a%20small%20object%20placed%20there%20will%20stay%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20travel%20time%20from%20launch%20to%20L1%20would%20take%20about%20four%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02120205%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-11.41.59-AM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02120205%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-11.41.59-AM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02120205%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-11.41.59-AM-300x157.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02120205%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-11.41.59-AM-1024x536.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671143%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20trajectory%20of%20the%20Aditya-L1%20mission.%20Photo%3A%20ISRO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20NASA%20and%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%20have%20sent%20numerous%20probes%20to%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20solar%20system%2C%20India%20is%20the%20first%20Asian%20nation%20to%20place%20an%20object%20in%20solar%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScientific%20objectives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ISRO%2C%20the%20major%20science%20objectives%20of%20the%20Aditya-L1%20mission%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStudy%20of%20Solar%20upper%20atmospheric%20(chromosphere%20and%20corona)%20dynamics.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStudy%20of%20chromospheric%20and%20coronal%20heating%2C%20physics%20of%20the%20partially%20ionized%20plasma%2C%20initiation%20of%20the%20coronal%20mass%20ejections%2C%20and%20flares.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EObserve%20the%20in-situ%20particle%20and%20plasma%20environment%20providing%20data%20for%20the%20study%20of%20particle%20dynamics%20from%20the%20Sun.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPhysics%20of%20solar%20corona%20and%20its%20heating%20mechanism.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDiagnostics%20of%20the%20coronal%20and%20coronal%20loops%20plasma%3A%20Temperature%2C%20velocity%20and%20density.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDevelopment%2C%20dynamics%20and%20origin%20of%20CMEs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIdentify%20the%20sequence%20of%20processes%20that%20occur%20at%20multiple%20layers%20(chromosphere%2C%20base%20and%20extended%20corona)%20which%20eventually%20leads%20to%20solar%20eruptive%20events.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMagnetic%20field%20topology%20and%20magnetic%20field%20measurements%20in%20the%20solar%20corona.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDrivers%20for%20space%20weather%20(origin%2C%20composition%20and%20dynamics%20of%20solar%20wind.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693636863000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02120229%2FScreenshot-2023-09-02-at-11.50.25-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Faditya-l1-isros-mission-to-study-the-sun-launched-successfully%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20mission%20to%20study%20the%20Sun's%20outermost%20layers%20represents%20another%20milestone%20for%20the%20Indian%20space%20programme%20after%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20successfully%20soft%20landed%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20on%20August%2023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A68%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Faditya-l1-isros-mission-to-study-the-sun-launched-successfully%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20BRICS%20Was%20Expanded%3A%20The%20Inside%20Story%20of%20Twists%20and%20Turns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24001805%2FF4NKlFIWcAAT_Qt.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20When%20it%20was%20announced%20that%20the%20bloc%20of%20emerging%20economies%20would%20more%20than%20double%20its%20group%20by%20adding%20six%20new%20members%2C%20it%20was%20a%20surprise%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20Inside%20the%20group%2C%20it%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20twists%20and%20turns%20to%20reach%20that%20decision.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESouth%20African%20President%20Cyril%20Ramaphosa%20declared%20at%20a%20press%20appearance%20with%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20other%20countries%20on%20August%2024%20that%20BRICS%20had%20invited%20Argentina%2C%20Egypt%2C%20the%20UAE%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Ethiopia%20and%20Iran.%20The%20doubling%20of%20a%20group%20in%20terms%20of%20numbers%20at%20one%20stroke%20was%20unprecedented%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%20had%20been%20advocating%20for%20bringing%20in%20new%20members%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20but%20the%20other%20countries%20had%20not%20displayed%20the%20same%20level%20of%20enthusiasm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20rather%20clear%20that%20India%20had%20been%20resisting%20an%20expansion%2C%20worried%20about%20the%20direction%20such%20a%20move%20would%20take.%20With%20China%20and%20then%20South%20Africa%20taking%20over%20the%20chairmanship%20in%20consecutive%20years%2C%20the%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20was%20getting%20clearer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20resistance%20was%20also%20worn%20down%20by%20the%20personal%20requests%20made%20by%20various%20countries%20who%20were%20vying%20to%20get%20in.%20While%20it%20was%20publicly%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20Iranian%20president%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-discusses-potential-expansion-of-brics-in-a-phone-call-with-iranian-president%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eengaged%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20regarding%20BRICS%2C%20similar%20approaches%20were%20made%20by%20various%20other%20nations.%20The%20mounting%20diplomatic%20pressure%20was%20becoming%20untenable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJust%20ahead%20of%20the%20summit%2C%20India%20claimed%20to%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37018%2FTranscript_of_Special_Briefing_by_Foreign_Secretary_on_Prime_Ministers_visit_to_South_Africa_and_Greece_August_21_2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epositive%20intent%20and%20an%20open%20mind%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20BRICS%20expansion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112451%2FH20230824137110.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112451%2FH20230824137110.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112451%2FH20230824137110-300x109.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112451%2FH20230824137110-1024x372.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671137%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22436%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20logo%20of%20the%20BRICS%20summit%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20South%20Africa.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20delegations%20arrived%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20all%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20except%20one%20%E2%80%93%20were%20prepared%20with%20an%20initial%20list%20of%20candidates%20for%20membership.%20Russia%20and%20South%20Africa%20had%20a%20list%20of%20three%20countries%2C%20China%20had%20four%20and%20India%2C%20somewhat%20unexpectedly%2C%20had%20the%20largest%20with%20five%20candidates.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20surprise%20to%20see%20the%20Indians%20with%20the%20biggest%20list%20after%20all%20the%20history%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20well-informed%20official%20of%20one%20of%20the%20BRICS%20members.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20country%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20list%20of%20names%20to%20put%20forward%20was%20Brazil.%20While%20President%20Luiz%20Inacio%20Lula%20da%20Silva%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20BRICS%20summit%20had%20even%20talked%20about%20supporting%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fbrics-summit-brazil-idAFKBN2ZX0XO%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EArgentina%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fbrazil-summit-brics-idAFS0N37802A%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVenezuela%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20diplomatic%20sources%20said%20that%20Brazilian%20officials%20did%20not%20furnish%20any%20candidates%20but%20left%20the%20final%20decision%20to%20their%20leadership.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20learnt%20that%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20initial%20list%20of%20priority%20candidates%20was%20Indonesia%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Argentina%2C%20while%20China%20had%20the%20same%20names%20with%20the%20addition%20of%20Egypt.%20India%E2%80%99s%20five%20names%20were%20those%20with%20whom%20it%20had%20a%20strategic%20partnership.%20It%20also%20included%20Indonesia%2C%20which%20withdrew%20from%20the%20race%20after%20all%20the%20members%20agreed%20to%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndonesian%20President%20Joko%20Widodo%20issued%20a%20statement%20on%20Thursday%2C%20after%20the%20expansion%20announcement%2C%20that%20Jakarta%20was%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20in%20a%20rush%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20wanted%20to%20%E2%80%9Cexamine%E2%80%9D%20the%20membership%20issues%20further.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESources%2C%20however%2C%20dismissed%20speculation%20that%20Indonesia%20was%20hesitant%20due%20to%20the%20perceived%20anti-West%20agenda%20of%20the%20group%2C%20noting%20that%20President%20Widodo%20had%20seemed%20happy%20enough%20in%20South%20Africa%20when%20he%20was%20informed%20about%20the%20green%20light%20for%20Jakarta%E2%80%99s%20entry.%20The%20official%20reason%20that%20Jakarta%20provided%20the%20BRICS%20members%20is%20that%20there%20were%20some%20internal%20approvals%20and%20rules%20for%20which%20it%20needed%20some%20ASEAN%20approval.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20sources%20insisted%20that%20Indonesia%20had%20apparently%20not%20formally%20applied%20for%20membership%2C%20even%20though%20it%20was%20on%20the%20top%20of%20the%20list%20of%20candidates.%20It%20had%20apparently%20expressed%20its%20interest%20verbally%20through%20China%20earlier.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20Indonesia%20withdrew%2C%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20came%20more%20sharply%20into%20the%20picture.%20China%20had%20been%20the%20strongest%20advocate%20for%20Saudi%20Arabia%20that%20also%20been%20vigorously%20lobbying%20for%20membership%2C%20but%20the%20other%20members%20felt%20that%20there%20needed%20to%20be%20a%20regional%20balance.%20Moreover%2C%20Iranian%20President%20Ebrahim%20Raisi%20had%20actively%20engaged%20in%20personal%20lobbying%20efforts%20with%20each%20member%20state%2C%20which%20made%20it%20diplomatically%20challenging%20to%20turn%20him%20down.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Russia%20had%20strongly%20supported%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20candidacy%2C%20to%20the%20surprise%20of%20many%2C%20China%20displayed%20hesitance.%20According%20to%20well-informed%20sources%2C%20China%20even%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20necessity%20of%20expanding%20the%20group%20by%20incorporating%20numerous%20new%20entrants.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20year%2C%20China%20had%20a%20major%20diplomatic%20victory%20in%20West%20Asia%2C%20when%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fmar%2F10%2Firan-saudi-arabia-agree-restore-ties-china-talks%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20brokered%20an%20agreement%20between%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Iran%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20restore%20diplomatic%20ties%20after%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20observers%20inferred%20from%20the%20negotiations%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20enthusiasm%20was%20somewhat%20dampened%2C%20possibly%20due%20to%20objections%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20This%20was%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Beijing%20and%20Riyadh%20having%20grown%20steadily%20closer%20in%20recent%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20appeared%20that%20the%20Saudis%20were%20also%20not%20too%20happy%20that%20the%20UAE%20was%20part%20of%20the%20new%20group.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20had%20also%20concluded%20that%20if%20Saudi%20Arabia%20was%20brought%20into%20BRICS%2C%20Iran%20could%20be%20the%20balance%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20learnt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20one%20time%20during%20the%20negotiations%2C%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20candidature%20made%20it%20almost%20seem%20like%20it%20was%20China%20versus%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20BRICS%20group%2C%20said%20a%20diplomatic%20source.%20Sensing%20the%20mood%20in%20the%20room%20and%20unwilling%20to%20be%20seen%20to%20obstruct%2C%20China%20acquiesced.%20It%20seemed%20that%20the%20candidate%20selection%20process%20was%20now%20done.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20final%20twist%20in%20the%20tale%20took%20place%20at%20the%20official%20dinner%20hosted%20by%20South%20Africa%20for%20the%20BRICS%20members%20and%20the%20other%20heads%20of%20state%20on%20the%20night%20of%20August%2023.%20Since%20the%20decision%20on%20the%20five%20countries%20had%20been%20already%20made%2C%20the%20participants%20at%20the%20dinner%20got%20an%20inkling%20of%20who%20made%20the%20cut.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20he%20learnt%20that%20his%20country%20was%20not%20on%20the%20list%2C%20Ethiopian%20Prime%20Minister%20Abiy%20Ahmed%20put%20his%20foot%20down%20during%20the%20dinner.%20He%20apparently%20conveyed%20that%20it%20was%20inconceivable%20that%20an%20African%20country%2C%20which%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccradle%20of%20humankind%E2%80%9D%20was%20not%20being%20included%20in%20the%20expanded%20BRICS.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20South%20African%20president%20then%20persuaded%20the%20other%20BRICS%20member%20that%20Ethiopia%20should%20be%20included%20at%20the%20last%20minute%20on%20Wednesday%20night%2C%20sources%20confirmed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112434%2FH20230824137104.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112434%2FH20230824137104.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112434%2FH20230824137104-300x171.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02112434%2FH20230824137104-1024x583.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671136%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EEthiopian%20Prime%20Minister%20Abiy%20Ahmed%20and%20Narendra%20Modi%20during%20the%2015th%20BRICS%20Summit%20at%20Johannesburg%2C%20in%20South%20Africa%20on%20August%2024%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20criteria%20for%20becoming%20a%20BRICS%20member%20has%20not%20been%20made%20public%20so%20far%2C%20with%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20terming%20it%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37049%2FTranscript_of_Special_Briefing_by_Foreign_Secretary_on_Prime_Ministers_visit_to_South_Africa_and_Greece_August_24_2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einternal%20document%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20an%20interview%2C%20the%20South%20African%20foreign%20minister%20Naledi%20Pandor%20said%20that%20the%20criteria%20used%20in%20selecting%20the%20new%20members%20included%20commitment%20to%20progressive%20ideas%2C%20recognising%20the%20UN%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpremier%20global%20institution%E2%80%9D%2C%20belief%20in%20peace%20and%20respect%20for%20international%20law.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20the%20BRICS%20countries%20come%20from%20backgrounds%20where%20we%20experienced%20colonialism%20and%20different%20forms%20of%20oppression%20so%20we%20believe%20in%20freedom%20and%20justice%20and%20the%20pursuit%20of%20equity%20and%20development.%20These%20are%20the%20underlying%20general%20principles%20that%20we%20elaborated%20on%20in%20the%20guideline%20document%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timeslive.co.za%2Fsunday-times%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2023-08-27-naledi-pandor-outlines-criteria-needed-to-become-a-member-of-brics%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshe%20said%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESources%20said%20that%20while%20these%20are%20the%20ideals%20that%20news%20members%20would%20agree%20with%2C%20there%20were%20also%20economic%20parameters%20that%20were%20drawn%20up.%20These%20included%20limits%20like%20trade%20with%20BRICS%20members%20at%20around%20%2450%20billion%20or%20a%20GDP%20of%20around%20%24400%20billion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20it%20was%20stressed%20that%20these%20were%20just%20general%20parameters.%20%E2%80%9CPotential%20members%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20meet%20all%20these%20economic%20criteria%2C%E2%80%9D%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693634517000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24001805%2FF4NKlFIWcAAT_Qt.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fbrics-expansion-inside-story%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20the%20delegations%20arrived%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20all%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20except%20one%20%E2%80%93%20were%20prepared%20with%20an%20initial%20list%20of%20candidates%20for%20membership.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fbrics-expansion-inside-story%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Importance%20of%20Being%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02103657%2FF3uRFgvW8AAhDHt.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20late%2C%20political%20observers%20have%20noticed%20the%20body%20language%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20when%20he%20is%20in%20the%20company%20of%C2%A0%20Congress%20President%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge.%20Rahul%20visibly%20displays%20a%20lot%20of%20respect%20and%20reverence%20for%20the%2081-year-old%20Congress%20veteran.%20A%20few%20days%20ago%2C%20Rahul%20made%20a%20public%20gesture%20at%20an%20event%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20where%20he%20sat%20beside%20the%20Congress%20president.%20Anticipating%20that%20he%20might%20be%20exhausted%20and%20thirsty%2C%20Rahul%20poured%20water%20into%20a%20glass%20and%20offered%20it%20to%20him.%20Some%20Congress%20spokespersons%20tweeted%20about%20this%20gesture.%20On%20another%20occasion%2C%20Rahul%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20personally%20drop%20off%20Kharge%20in%20his%20own%20car%20after%20a%20Congress%20party%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20citing%20these%20instances%20only%20to%20underline%20that%20a%20special%20relationship%20is%20being%20forged%20between%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge.%20Clearly%2C%20Rahul%20has%20not%20displayed%20such%20respect%20and%20affection%20in%20public%20towards%20any%20other%20veteran%20Congress%20leader.%20This%20has%20some%20serious%20political%20import%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20which%20has%20gathered%20considerable%20momentum%20over%20the%20past%20few%20months.%20As%20a%20veteran%20in%20Indian%20politics%2C%20the%20role%20that%20Kharge%20has%20played%20in%20softening%20the%20rough%20edges%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20is%20quite%20apparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKharge%20has%20much%20more%20going%20in%20his%20favour.%20He%20is%20a%20Dalit%20leader%20from%20the%20South%20and%20does%20not%20threaten%20caste-based%20leaders%20from%20the%20north%20Indian%20Hindi%20heartland%2C%20where%20identity%20politics%20still%20creates%20immense%20hostilities%20over%20turf.%20History%20does%20tell%20us%20that%20whenever%20there%20is%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20decisive%20mandate%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20a%20non-threatening%20leader%20from%20the%20South%20emerges%20as%20a%20consensus%20candidate%20in%20a%20non-BJP%20coalition.%20Of%20course%2C%20this%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20apply%20to%20a%20BJP-led%20coalition%2C%20because%20it%20is%20a%20largely%20north%20Indian%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EP.V.%20Narasimha%20Rao%20emerged%20as%20the%20consensus%20PM%20candidate%20after%20the%20Congress%20fell%20short%20of%20a%20majority%20in%201991.%20Within%20the%20Congress%2C%20there%20were%20more%20powerful%20leaders%20from%20the%20North%20but%20the%20relatively%20low-profile%20Narasimha%20Rao%20emerged%20as%20a%20consensus%20candidate.%20The%20same%20could%20be%20said%20about%20dark%20horse%20Deve%20Gowda%2C%20whom%20both%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20and%20Mulayam%20Singh%20Yadav%20supported%20to%20lead%20the%20United%20Front%20coalition.%20Neither%20of%20these%20leaders%20threatened%20cowbelt%20political%20equations%20in%20any%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20in%20this%20context%20that%20Kharge%E2%80%99s%20importance%20must%20be%20underlined%20as%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20goes%20into%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20If%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20base%20case%20improves%20to%20above%20100%20seats%2C%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20could%20throw%20up%20surprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%202024%20is%20not%202019%20and%20PM%20Modi%20will%20surely%20be%20judged%20by%20the%20people%20on%20his%2010-year%20performance%2C%20irrespective%20of%20whether%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20has%20an%20alternative%20PM%20candidate.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20voter%20psychology%20was%20to%20give%20Modi%20another%20five%20years.%20But%20this%20time%20round%2C%20many%20Modi%20voters%20may%20also%20think%20that%2010%20years%20is%20a%20long%20time%20for%20a%20leader%20to%20show%20results.%20So%20results%20are%20what%20a%20large%20number%20of%20voters%20will%20look%20for%2C%20a%20noisy%20Hindutva%20campaign%20notwithstanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20with%20optimal%20seat-sharing%20across%20the%20country%2C%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20can%20put%20up%20a%20fight%20if%20the%20election%20is%20purely%20a%20referendum%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%2010%20years%20in%20power%2C%20and%20what%20he%20has%20done%20for%20economic%20and%20social%20welfare%2C%20in%20concrete%20terms.%20There%20is%20clearly%20some%20nervousness%20in%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%95%20a%20desperate%20PM%20is%20publicly%20announcing%20unfilled%20government%20vacancies%20and%20internal%20promotions%20dressed%20up%20as%20new%20jobs!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20need%20not%20project%20a%20PM%20candidate%2C%20but%20the%20message%20could%20be%20gently%20delivered%20that%20if%20the%20Congress%20emerges%20as%20the%20single%20largest%20party%20within%20the%20alliance%2C%20with%20about%20110%20-120%20seats%2C%20then%20Kharge%20could%20emerge%20as%20a%20consensus%20candidate%20to%20lead%20a%20possible%20coalition.%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20seems%20to%20be%20mentally%20preparing%20for%20this%20possibility.%20By%20doing%20so%2C%20Rahul%20may%20also%20be%20signalling%20that%20he%20is%20firmly%20out%20of%20the%20race%20to%20lead%20the%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20young%20Gandhi%20has%20always%20imagined%20building%20a%20credible%20Dalit%20leadership%20to%20impart%20some%20freshness%20and%20new%20energy%20to%20the%20grand%20old%20party.%20Kharge%20fits%20the%20bill%20perfectly.%20Besides%2C%20it%20will%20be%20very%20difficult%20for%20other%20INDIA%20alliance%20partners%20or%20even%20someone%20outside%20it%20like%20Mayawati%2C%20to%20oppose%20Kharge%20as%20a%20post-election%20leader%20of%20the%20coalition.%20The%20next%20seven%20months%20could%20throw%20up%20interesting%20possibilities.%20Politics%20is%2C%20after%20all%2C%20the%20art%20of%20the%20possible!%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693631394000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F02103657%2FF3uRFgvW8AAhDHt.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-importance-of-being-mallikarjun-kharge%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20veteran%20in%20Indian%20politics%2C%20the%20role%20that%20the%20Congress%20president%20has%20played%20in%20softening%20the%20rough%20edges%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20is%20quite%20apparent.%20Kharge%20has%20a%20lot%20going%20in%20his%20favour.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-importance-of-being-mallikarjun-kharge%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20launches%20first%20mission%20to%20the%20sun%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693626060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F09%2F768x432%2Fskynews-india-space_6271239.jpg%3F20230902072329%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Findia-launches-rocket-towards-the-sun-after-successful-moon-lander-mission-12952814%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ten%20days%20after%20India's%20success%20in%20landing%20the%20first%20ever%20spacecraft%20on%20the%20southern%20side%20of%20the%20moon%2C%20the%20country%20has%20launched%20'Aditya%20L1'%2C%20its%20first%20mission%20to%20study%20the%20sun.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5846%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Findia-launches-rocket-towards-the-sun-after-successful-moon-lander-mission-12952814%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Findia-launches-rocket-towards-the-sun-after-successful-moon-lander-mission-12952814%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Findia-launches-rocket-towards-the-sun-after-successful-moon-lander-mission-12952814%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LPG%20Price%20Cut%3A%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Rakhi%20%E2%80%98Gift%E2%80%99%20Ends%20Up%20Drawing%20Attention%20to%20Inflation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F06%2FModi-LPG.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20The%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20reduce%20liquefied%20petroleum%20gas%20of%20LPG%20cylinder%20prices%20by%20Rs%20200%2C%20pegged%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9CRakhi%20gift%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20women%20of%20the%20country%20has%20drawn%20sharp%20criticism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOpposition%20parties%20and%20analysts%20have%20accused%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20of%20attempting%20%E2%80%9Ca%20poll%20gimmick%E2%80%9D%20ahead%20of%20key%20state%20elections%20later%20this%20year%20and%20the%20general%20elections%20in%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrior%20to%20the%20Rs%20200%20subsidy%20now%20being%20offered%2C%20the%20price%20of%20one%20cylinder%20was%20a%20whopping%20Rs%201%2C103%20in%20New%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20Union%20government%20itself%20having%20told%20parliament%20in%20July%20that%20the%20price%20of%20subsidised%20LPG%20cylinder%20in%20January%202014%20was%20Rs%20414%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98cut%E2%80%99%20is%20actually%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20the%20price%20of%20this%20vital%20necessity%20that%20has%20risen%20sharply%20since%202014.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EGas%3A%20What%20government%20is%20saying%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20Union%20minister%20for%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20Anurag%20Thakur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fianuragthakur%2Fstatus%2F1696481717366972674%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eannounced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20packaged%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9CRakhi%20gift%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%20auspicious%20occasion%20of%20Onam%20and%20Raksha%20Bandhan%2C%20prime%20minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20as%20he%20is%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98bhai%E2%80%99%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20given%20a%20gift%20to%20the%20millions%20and%20millions%20of%20sisters%20and%20users%20of%20LPG%20cylinders.%20The%20prices%20of%20the%20LPG%20cylinders%20for%20domestic%20use%20has%20been%20brought%20down%20by%20Rs%20200%20per%20cylinder%20for%20each%20and%20every%20user.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2075%20lakh%20new%20gas%20connections%20will%20be%20given%20under%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%20scheme%20that%20will%20take%20up%20the%20total%20connections%20to%2010.35%20crores%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELaunched%20on%20May%201%2C%202016%2C%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%20or%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fin-fy23-lpg-refills-under-ujjwala-fell-12-of-beneficiaries-didnt-get-a-single-refill-govt%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EPMUY%20aimed%20to%20provide%20deposit-free%20LPG%20connections%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20adult%20women%20from%20poor%20households%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Ujjwala%20Yojana%20beneficiaries%20they%20are%20already%20getting%20Rs%20200%20subsidy%20as%20DBT