20World%20Resources%20Institute%20(WRI)%20India%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1838002%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epiloting%20different%20Nature-based%20solutions%20(NbS)%3C%2Fa%3E%20aimed%20at%20making%20communities%20more%20resilient%20to%20climate%20change.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENbS%20interventions%20not%20only%20improve%20urban%20environmental%20ecosystems%2C%20but%20also%20offer%20social%20and%20economic%20benefits%20to%20communities%20by%20creating%20healthy%20spaces%20for%20recreation%2C%20and%20by%20opening%20up%20opportunities%20for%20skilling%20up%20and%20livelihood%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20are%20low-income%20groups%20so%20much%20more%20vulnerable%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Pramila%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20a%20community%20organiser%20and%20advisor%20at%20SIDART%2C%20an%20organisation%20that%20works%20for%20the%20upliftment%20of%20women%20and%20children%20%E2%80%94%20says%20that%20water%20scarcity%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20of%20the%20city%2C%20and%20flooding%20during%20monsoons%20has%20now%20become%20extremely%20common.%20%E2%80%9CUrbanisation%20has%20impacted%20natural%20biodiversity%2C%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20forests%20and%20hills%20being%20cut%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20rising%20fluctuations%20and%20climatic%20changes%20affect%20low-income%20groups%20due%20to%20a%20combination%20of%20socio-economic%20and%20demographic%20factors.%20During%20the%202005%20Mumbai%20floods%2C%20over%20a%20million%20slum%20residents%20were%20stranded.%20These%20are%20the%20neighbourhoods%20that%20often%20lack%20access%20to%20basic%20services%20and%20amenities%20like%20potable%20water%2C%20energy%2C%20sanitation.%20For%20instance%2C%2084.9%25%20of%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s%20M-East%20ward%20population%20lives%20in%20slu